            <div corresp="#c4230f2">
                <head>RUANDA - district, E. Africa between Belgium Congo and Tanganyika; formerly
                    part of German East Africa; since 1919 associated with Urundi ad Ruanda-Urundi
                    and administered by Belgium, as a League of Nations Mandate 1919-1945. Asia UN
                    trust territory since 1946.</head>
                <p>Department Mailing Notice of Nov. 2, 1960. The first American Consulate has been
                    established in the U.N. Trust Territory of Ruanda-Urundi which is under Belgian
                    Administration.</p>
                <p>The name of the capital city of the Kingdom of Burundi was changed from Usumbura
                    to Bujumbura in the constitution drawn up by the newly independent country. The
                    Department of State concurred with the U.S. Board on Geographic Names to
                    recognize this change on March 6, 1964.</p>
            </div>
